
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `docker-compose` baraye ejra va modiriat barname-haye Docker ke az chand container tashkil shode-and estefade mishavad. Ba estefade az yek file `docker-compose.yml`, mitoonid hameye container-ha, network-ha va volume-ha ra ba ham tarif konid va be soorati yekparche ejra konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `docker-compose up`  --> 🚀 Container-ha ra misazad va ejra mikonad.
    🔹 `docker-compose down`  --> ⛔ Container-ha, network-ha va volume-ha ra pak mikonad.
    🔹 `docker-compose ps`  --> ℹ️ Vaziat container-ha ra neshon midahad.
    🔹 `docker-compose logs`  --> 📝 Log-haye container-ha ra neshon midahad.
    🔹 `docker-compose exec [service] [command]` --> 💻 Dastoor ra dar yek container ejra mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ docker-compose up -d

    🔹 Container-ha ra dar paszamine (detached mode) ejra mikonad.

    $ docker-compose down

    🔹 Hameye container-ha ra motavaqef mikonad va network-ha va volume-ha ra hazf mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ docker-compose logs web

    🔹 Log-haye service ba name `web` ra neshon midahad, baraye peyda kardan error-ha mofid ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `docker-compose` command is used to run and manage multi-container Docker applications. Using a `docker-compose.yml` file, you can define all your containers, networks, and volumes together and run them in a single command.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `docker-compose up`  --> 🚀 Builds and starts the containers.
    🔹 `docker-compose down`  --> ⛔ Stops and removes containers, networks, and volumes.
    🔹 `docker-compose ps`  --> ℹ️ Shows the status of the containers.
    🔹 `docker-compose logs`  --> 📝 Shows the logs of the containers.
    🔹 `docker-compose exec [service] [command]` --> 💻 Executes a command in a running container.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ docker-compose up -d

    🔹 Runs the containers in detached mode (background).

    $ docker-compose down

    🔹 Stops all containers and removes the networks and volumes.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ docker-compose logs web

    🔹 Shows the logs for the service named `web`, useful for debugging errors.
